  "prompt": "What is luvox good for?",
  "response": "Luvox, known generically as fluvoxamine, is a medication primarily used to treat obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD). It is classified as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) and works by increasing the levels of serotonin in the brain. Serotonin is a neurotransmitter that plays a key role in mood regulation, and higher levels of serotonin can help reduce the symptoms of OCD.\n\nIn addition to OCD, Luvox may also be prescribed for other conditions such as social anxiety disorder, depression, and certain forms of anxiety. As with any medication, it is important to follow a healthcare provider\u2019s recommendations and guidelines when using Luvox to manage your symptoms and conditions.",
